songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
We had a lot of good times when we were together
And I thought we'd last forever, you and I
I.M. for so long, I couldn't wait to get you're phone call
Dreaming 'bout you makes me feel alright
Tonight you called me on the phone
Said you had to stay at home
Is there something I should know? Yeah

[Chorus]
I was fine 'til 7:05
'Til she walked out the door and right out of my life
If you're gone, I'll move on
But it only would have taken two seconds to say
Goodbye (Goodbye), Goodbye (Goodbye)
Goodbye, whoa-oh

[Verse 2]
The night after you're phone call
Me and friends were hanging at the mall
I was not believing what I saw, whoa
Holding hands with him and sitting closer then six inches
Hoping she's not gonna kiss him now
How can I call you a friend? You stood me up in the end
I know that it's over, yeah

[Chorus]
I was fine 'til 7:05
'Til she walked out the door and right out of my life
If you're gone, I'll move on
But it only would have taken two seconds to say
Goodbye (Goodbye), Goodbye (Goodbye)
Goodbye, whoa-oh

[Bridge]
Don't keep telling me that you're sorry now
But let me tell you how much this hurts me too
Yeah, oh

[Chorus][x2]
I was fine 'til 7:05
'Til she walked out the door and right out of my life
If you're gone, I'll move on
But it only would have taken two seconds to say
Goodbye, goodbye, goodbye, whoa-oh
I was fine 'til 7:05
'Til she walked out the door and right out of my life
If you're gone, I'll move on
But it only would have taken two seconds to say
Goodbye (Goodbye), Goodbye (Goodbye)
Goodbye

[Outro]
But it only would have taken two seconds to say
Goodbye (Goodbye), Goodbye (Goodbye), whoa-oh
Goodbye
